
Overview of noun elixir

The noun elixir has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. elixir -- (a sweet flavored liquid (usually containing a small amount of alcohol) used in compounding medicines to be taken by mouth in order to mask an unpleasant taste)
2. philosopher's stone, philosophers' stone, elixir -- (hypothetical substance that the alchemists believed to be capable of changing base metals into gold)
3. elixir -- (a substance believed to cure all ills)
